{{Infobox journal | title = Bogoslovni vestnik | cover = BogoslovniVestnik-08-1 1.jpg | image_size = 200px | discipline = [[Theology]] | language = [[English language|English]], [[French language|French]], [[German language|German]], [[Italian language|Italian]], [[Latin]], [[Slovene language|Slovene]] | abbreviation = Bogosl. Vestn. | editor = Robert Petkovšek | publisher = Faculty of Theology, [[University of Ljubljana]] | country = Slovenia | frequency = Quarterly | history = 1920–1945; 1965–present | website = http://www.teof.uni-lj.si/bv.html | ISSN = 0006-5722 | eISSN = 1581-2987 | OCLC = 439849909 | LCCN = 76525121 }} '''''Bogoslovni vestnik''''', subtitled ''Theological Quarterly, Ephemerides Theologicae'', is a quarterly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] on [[theology]] published by the Faculty of Theology of the [[University of Ljubljana]]. It is the oldest [[Slovenia]]n scholarly journal in the field of [[humanities]].<ref name="Presentation">{{cite web |url=http://www.teof.uni-lj.si/uploads/File/BV/BV_General_Presentation.pdf |title=Bogoslovni vestnik: General Presentation |publisher=University of Ljubljana, Faculty of Theology |accessdate=30 January 2012}}</ref> Articles are in [[English language|English]], [[French language|French]], [[German language|German]], [[Italian language|Italian]], [[Latin]], or [[Slovene language|Slovenian]].<ref name="Presentation" /> The journal is abstracted in ''[[Religious and Theological Abstracts]]''.<ref>[http://rtabstracts.org/journals-we-abstract.php ''Religious and Theological Abstracts'': Journals We Abstract]</ref>
